   134→  "text": "In the LLVM optimization pass system, pass registration and execution follows a templated, concept-based polymorphism pattern:

## PassManager Template (llvm/include/llvm/IR/PassManager.h)
The core PassManager is a template class parameterized by IRUnitT (e.g., Module, Function). It implements addPass<PassT>() which wraps each pass in a PassModel<IRUnitT, PassT> that derives from PassConcept. Passes are stored as unique_ptr<PassConcept> in a vector.

## PassConcept and PassModel (llvm/include/llvm/IR/PassManagerInternal.h)
PassConcept is an abstract base class defining the polymorphic run() interface. PassModel is a template that wraps any pass class and implements the concept, calling the pass's run() method. This enables storing heterogeneous pass types in a single container.

## PassInfoMixin (llvm/include/llvm/IR/PassManager.h)
All pass classes derive from PassInfoMixin<DerivedT>, which provides name() and printPipeline() methods. Example: InstCombinePass : public PassInfoMixin<InstCombinePass> (llvm/include/llvm/Transforms/InstCombine/InstCombine.h)

## Pass Registration via PassRegistry.def (llvm/lib/Passes/PassRegistry.def)
Passes are defined using MODULE_PASS, FUNCTION_PASS, CGSCC_PASS, and LOOP_PASS macros that map string names to pass constructors (e.g., MODULE_PASS("instcombine", InstCombinePass()))

## Optimization Pipeline (llvm/lib/Passes/PassBuilderPipelines.cpp)
The O2/O3 pipeline is constructed through buildPerModuleDefaultPipeline() which calls:
- buildModuleSimplificationPipeline() - adds early optimization passes
- buildModuleOptimizationPipeline() - adds main optimization passes including ControlHeightReduction (O3 only), loop passes, vectorization, and global optimizations

Passes are added via MPM.addPass(PassInstance()), which creates PassModel wrappers and stores them in the PassManager's Passes vector.

## Pass Parsing and Lookup (llvm/lib/Passes/PassBuilder.cpp)
parseModulePass() looks up pass names in PassRegistry.def using a macro-expanded switch statement. When a match is found, it instantiates the pass and calls MPM.addPass() to add it to the pipeline.

## Execution (llvm/include/llvm/IR/PassManagerImpl.h)
PassManager<IRUnitT>::run() iterates through all Passes, calling Pass->run(IR, AnalysisManager) for each. Each pass's PreservedAnalyses return value is used to invalidate cached analyses. This enables the dependency-aware, lazy evaluation of analysis passes."
